1FUNC     WYLBUR Functions                                                                                                  Page    5
0D-Loc  Object Code    Addr1 Addr2  Stmt Lv Lineno    Source Statement           (Hibal 5, Asmedit 3.3)  HLASM R4.0  2004/03/15 12.45
+_____  ______ ____    _____ _____  ____ __ ______    ______ _________
0                                   1014              * LAST UPDATE 7/89
                                    1015              *******************************************************************
                                    1016              **                                                             ****
                                    1017              **                                                              ***
                                    1018              **      HOW TO ADD A SYSTEM VARIABLE OR FUNCTION !               **
                                    1019              ***     ------------------------------------------               **
                                    1020              *****                                                            **
                                    1021              *******************************************************************
                                    1022              *
                                    1023              *  PROCEDURE TO ADD VARIABLE OR FUNCTION:
                                    1024              *
                                    1025              *  1. ADD A ENTRY INTO THE SYSTEM VARIABLE/FUNCTION TABLE.
                                    1026              *
                                    1027              *       THIS TABLE (SYSFNS) IS SEARCHED TO FIND THE ADDRESS OF
                                    1028              *       THE ROUTINE FOR THE SPECIFIED FUNCTION, VARIABLE, OR
                                    1029              *       PROC.  THE ENTRIES MUST APPEAR IN ALPHABETICAL ORDER.
                                    1030              *       USE THE 'SYSFN'    AND  'SYSVAR'   MACRO TO CREATE A
                                    1031              *       PROPERLY FORMATTED ENTRY.
                                    1032              *
                                    1033              *  2. ADD A SYSTEM VARIABLE/FUNCTION ROUTINE.
                                    1034              *
                                    1035              *       SYSTEM VARIABLE/FUNCTION ROUTINES ARE FOUND AFTER THE
                                    1036              *       SYSTEM VARIABLE/FUNCTION TABLE. THE ROUTINES SHOULD BE
                                    1037              *       PLACED IN ALPHABETICAL ORDER BASED ON THE VAR/FUNC
                                    1038              *       KEYWORD.  WORK AND COMMON ROUTINES SHOULD BE PLACED
                                    1039              *       IN ALPHABETICAL ORDER IN THE COMMON/WORK ROUTINES AREA.
                                    1040              *       THE BASIC ENTRY AND EXIT CONVENTIONS ARE:
                                    1041              *
                                    1042              *       ON ENTRY:
                                    1043              *            R0 - VARIABLE COUNT
                                    1044              *            R1 - ARGUMENT LIST
                                    1045              *            R6 - FUNCTION/VARIABLE RETURN AREA
                                    1046              *                 (AREA WILL INITIALLY CONTAIN VAR/FUNC/PROC NAME)
                                    1047              *
                                    1048              *       ON EXIT:
                                    1049              *            R6 - RETURNED VALUE (SAME AS ON ENTRY)
                                    1050              *           R15 - CC=ZERO, ALL OK
                                    1051              *                 CC=NZ, IF ERROR,,, ERROR MSG TSEG 'D
                                    1052              *
                                    1053              *       THE FORMAT OF THE ARGUMENTS PASSED AND RETURNED IS
                                    1054              *       DESCRIBED BY THE VNENTRY DSECT.  EACH ARGUMENT OCCUPIES
                                    1055              *       A FIXED LENGTH (L'VPARM) ENTRY. THUS EACH INPUT
                                    1056              *       ARGUMENT (IF ANY) CAN BE EASILY FOUND AT A FIXED OFFSET
                                    1057              *       BASED OFF OF R1.
                                    1058              *
                                    1059              *       SEVERAL MACROS EXIST TO MAKE THE ADDITION OF ROUTINES
                                    1060              *       EASIER.  TO USE THESE MACROS CERTAIN ADDITIONAL
                                    1061              *       CONVENTIONS MUST BE ADHERED TO.  THESE CONVENTIONS AND
                                    1062              *       THE MACROS ARE DESCRIBED NOW:
                                    1063              *
                                    1064              *   *** AN 'PROC' AND A 'PEND' MUST
                                    1065              *       BE USED TO ENTER AND EXIT THE ROUTINE.
                                    1066              *
                                    1067              *   *** IF THE ROUTINE IS SUCCESSFUL R15 MUST BE RETURNED
                                    1068              *       EQUAL TO ZERO.  IF NOT R15 MUST BE RETURNED AS NON-ZERO
                                    1069              *       (4).  ALSO AN APPROPRIATE ERROR MESSAGE MUST BE TSEG'D.
1FUNC     WYLBUR Functions                                                                                                  Page    6
0D-Loc  Object Code    Addr1 Addr2  Stmt Lv Lineno    Source Statement           (Hibal 5, Asmedit 3.3)  HLASM R4.0  2004/03/15 12.45
+_____  ______ ____    _____ _____  ____ __ ______    ______ _________
0                                   1070              *       ** DO NOT EXIT A ROUTINE VIA CVNEXT OR CVERROR !! **
                                    1071              *
                                    1072              *   *** IF YOU INTEND TO USE THE "SCANNER", YOU MUST SAVE AND
                                    1073              *       RESTORE THE CURRENT SCANNER STATE.  FOR AN EXAMPLE SEE
                                    1074              *       'YESNO' ROUTINE.
                                    1075              *
                                    1076              *   *** THE 'SETARGS' MACRO.
                                    1077              *
                                    1078              *       TO CHECK ENTRY ARGUMENTS, THE 'SETARGS' MACRO IS
                                    1079              *       PROVIDED.  IT TAKES A SINGLE STRING AS A PARAMETER.
                                    1080              *       THE FIRST TWO CHARACTERS OF THIS STRING DEFINE THE
                                    1081              *       MAXIMUM AND MINIMUM NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS THAT THE
                                    1082              *       ROUTINE WILL TAKE.  THE REMAINING CHARACTERS DESCRIBE
                                    1083              *       THE FORMAT THAT THESE ARGUMENTS SHOULD BE CONVERTED TO:
                                    1084              *       S=STRING, I=INTEGER, W=LINE NUMBER, X=DON'T CARE.  FOR
                                    1085              *       AN EXAMPLE SEE THE 'FNSUBSTR' ROUTINE.  NOTE THAT THE
                                    1086              *       'SETARGS' MACRO CALLS A SETARGS ROUTINE.  THIS ROUTINE
                                    1087              *       ASSUMES THAT R0,R1 AND R6 ARE THE SAME AS WHEN THE
                                    1088              *       SYSTEM VAR/FUNC ROUTINE WAS CALLED.  'SETARGS' ALSO
                                    1089              *       WILL GIVE A NON-ZERO RETURN CODE AND TSEG A ERROR
                                    1090              *       MESSAGE IF THE ARGUMENTS CANNOT BE CONVERTED TO THE
                                    1091              *       REQUIRED FORMAT. THE 'SETARGS' MACRO DOES NOT HANDLE
                                    1092              *       'ARRAYS' OR 'PACKED' NUMBERS.
                                    1093              *
                                    1094              *   *** THE 'BADARG' MACRO
                                    1095              *
                                    1096              *       ERROR MESSAGES CAN BE GENERATED
                                    1097              *       WITH THE 'BADARG' MACRO.  THE MACRO TAKES A SINGLE
                                    1098              *       NUMBER AS A PARAMETER.  THIS NUMBER IS THE NUMBER OF
                                    1099              *       THE INVALID ARGUMENT.  THIS MACRO REQUIRES THAT R6 AND
                                    1100              *       THE AREA POINTED TO BY R6 BE THE SAME AS WHEN THE
                                    1101              *       SYSTEM VAR/FUNC ROUTINE WAS ENTERED.  FOR AN EXAMPLE
                                    1102              *       SEE THE 'FNSUBSTR' ROUTINE.
                                    1103              *
                                    1104              *   *** THE 'VRETURN' MACRO
                                    1105              *
                                    1106              *       THE 'VRETURN' MACRO IS USED TO RETURN A VARIABLE OR
                                    1107              *       FUNCTION VALUE.  IT TAKES 2-3 PARAMETERS. THE FIRST IS
                                    1108              *       THE TYPE OF VALUE TO RETURN.  THIS MAY BE STRING,
                                    1109              *       INTEGER, LINENO, OR BOOLEAN.  ARRAYS AND PACKED NUMBERS
                                    1110              *       MAY NOT BE RETURNED WITH THIS MACRO.  ARGUMENTS 2-3 ARE
                                    1111              *       THE VALUE OF THE VAR/FUNC.  IF THE TYPE IS A STRING:
                                    1112              *       ARGS 2-3 ARE THE STRING LOC, LENGTH; A QUOTED STRING
                                    1113              *       MAY BE RETURNED, THE CONVENTIONS FOR RETURNING A STRING
                                    1114              *       ARE THE SAME AS FOR THE 'MSG' MACRO.  IF THE TYPE IS
                                    1115              *       INTEGER OR LINENO: THE SECOND PARAMETER IS A FULLWORD
                                    1116              *       VALUE.  IF THE TYPE IS BOOLEAN: THE SECOND PARAMETER IS
                                    1117              *       THE WORD 'TRUE' OR THE WORD 'FALSE'.  THIS MACRO
                                    1118              *       REQUIRES THAT R6 BE THE SAME AS WHEN THE SYSTEM
                                    1119              *       VAR/FUNC. ROUTINE WAS ENTERED.  FOR EXAMPLES, SEE THE
                                    1120              *       'FNCASE' 'FNLENGTH' 'FNLILB' 'FNLAST' AND 'FNTRUE'.
                                    1121              *       SOME ISOLATED EXAMPLES ARE:
                                    1122              *             VRETURN STRING,' THIS IS IT '
                                    1123              *             VRETURN STRING,(R1),(R0)
                                    1124              *             VRETURN BOOLEAN,TRUE
                                    1125              *             VRETURN LINENO,L:XXLINENO
1FUNC     WYLBUR Functions                                                                                                  Page    7
0D-Loc  Object Code    Addr1 Addr2  Stmt Lv Lineno    Source Statement           (Hibal 5, Asmedit 3.3)  HLASM R4.0  2004/03/15 12.45
+_____  ______ ____    _____ _____  ____ __ ______    ______ _________
0                                   1126              *             VRETURN INTEGER,(R4)
                                    1127              *       HEY DUDE !! THE VRETURN MACRO CLOBBERS R15,R0,R1,R2 SO
                                    1128              *       BE CAREFUL.  R15 IS SET TO ZERO BY THE VRETURN MACRO.
                                    1129              *
                                    1130              *   *** THE 'VTRIM' MACRO
                                    1131              *
                                    1132              *       THE 'VTRIM' MACRO IS USED TO TRIM TRAILING BLANKS OFF
                                    1133              *       THE END OF RETURNED STINGS.  IT WILL ALSO SET BLANK OR
                                    1134              *       ZEROED STRINGS TO NULL STRINGS.  IT REQUIRES THAT R6 BE
                                    1135              *       THE SAVE AS WHEN THE SYSTEM FUNC/VAR ROUTINE WAS
                                    1136              *       ENTERED.  IT IS GENERALLY CODED DIRECTLY FOLLOWING THE
                                    1137              *       'VRETURN STRING,..' MACRO.  FOR AN EXAMPLE SEE 'FNLIB'
                                    1138              *       ROUTINE.
                                    1139              *
                                    1140              *   *** GENERAL ARGUMENT LOADING/CHECKING PROCEDURES
                                    1141              *
                                    1142              *       ARGUMENTS PASSED TO A ROUTINE ARE GENERALLY CHECKED FOR
                                    1143              *       VALIDITY AT THE VERY BEGINNING OF THE ROUTINE WITH THE
                                    1144              *       'SETARGS' MACRO.  THE ARGUMENTS ARE THEN LOADED AND
                                    1145              *       CHECKED (WHILE THE ENTRY REGS ARE STILL SET UP)
                                    1146              *       GENERALLY AS FOLLOWS:  (THIS IS AN EXAMPLE ONLY, OH
                                    1147              *       YEAH:)
                                    1148              *
                                    1149              *       FNX      PROC  ,
                                    1150              *                SETARGS '22SI'            2 ARGS: STRING, INTEGER
                                    1151              *                IF    Z,BEGIN             IF ARGS OK,...
                                    1152              *                USING VNENTRY,R5
                                    1153              *                LA    R5,ARG1(R1)         R5 - 1ST ARG POINTER
                                    1154              *                LA    R2,VNSTRLOC         R2 - LOC OF STRING
                                    1155              *                LH    R3,VNSTRLEN         R3 - LEN OF STRING
                                    1156              *                IF    (R3,GT,120),BEGIN
                                    1157              *                BADARG 1                  PRETEND CHECK FOR STR LEN
                                    1158              *                EXIT  FNX
                                    1159              *                END
                                    1160              *                LA    R5,ARG2(R1)         R5 - 2ND ARG POINTER
                                    1161              *                L     R4,VNVALUE          R4 - INTEGER VALUE
                                    1162              *                IF    ((R4,NEG),OR,(R4,GT,120)),BEGIN
                                    1163              *                BADARG 2                  PRETEND CHECK FOR ARG 2
                                    1164              *                EXIT  FNX
                                    1165              *                END
                                    1166              *                ..... AND SO ON
                                    1167              *
                                    1168              *
                                    1169              *                ... END OF ROUTINE, XEXIT ...
                                    1170              *
                                    1171              *
                                    1172              *   *** RETURNING VAR/FUNCTION VALUE,,,
                                    1173              *
                                    1174              *       THE EASY WAY IS WITH THE 'VRETURN MACRO', BUT THERE ARE
                                    1175              *       OTHER WAYS.  YOU MAY SET UP YOUR OWN RETURN VALUE @R6.
                                    1176              *       SEE VNENTRY DSECT. THE AREA MUST BE CLEARED.  FLAGS
                                    1177              *       MUST BE SET FOR THE VARIABLE TYPE:  STRING, BOOLEAN,
                                    1178              *       NUMBER.  THE VARIABLE VALUE MUST BE SET.  FOR EXAMPLES,
                                    1179              *       SEE 'FNASCII' 'FNPI' OR 'FNSUBSTR'.  IF YOU WANT TO
                                    1180              *       DEAL WITH ARRAYS (IF THEY EXIST),,, GOOD LUCK HASBRO !!
                                    1181              *
1FUNC     WYLBUR Functions                                                                                                  Page    8

0                                   1182              *   *** FINAL ADVICE
                                    1183              *
                                    1184              *       THIS MODULE ADHERES TO SEVERAL CONVENTIONS.  IF YOU
                                    1185              *       ADHERE TO THESE CONVENTIONS, IT WILL MAKE IT EASIER FOR
                                    1186              *       YOU AND ALL THE PEOPLE WHO ALSO WANT TO ADD VARS/FUNCS
                                    1187              *       TO ADD THEM. IT IS WORTH IT TO TAKE A BIT OF TIME AND
                                    1188              *       LOOK AT HOW SEVERAL EXITING SYSTEM VARIABLE/FUNCTION
                                    1189              *       ROUTINES ARE CODED.
                                    1190              *
                                    1191              *   *** SOME DOCUMENTATION
                                    1192              *
                                    1193              *        ON ENTRY:
                                    1194              *             R0 - VARIABLE COUNT
                                    1195              *             R1 - ARGUMENT LIST
                                    1196              *             R6 - FUNCTION/VARIABLE RETURN AREA
                                    1197              *                  (AREA WILL INITIALLY CONTAIN VAR/FUNC/PROC NAME)
                                    1198              *
                                    1199              *
                                    1200              *        ON EXIT:
                                    1201              *             R6 - RETURNED VALUE (SAME AS ON ENTRY)
                                    1202              *            R15 - CC=ZERO, ALL OK
                                    1203              *                  CC=NZ, IF ERROR,,, ERROR MSG TSEG 'D
                                    1204              *
                                    1205              *        ARG1     EQU   0*L'VPARM           USUALLY @R1
                                    1206              *        ARG2     EQU   1*L'VPARM
                                    1207              *        ARG3     EQU   2*L'VPARM
                                    1208              *        ARG4     EQU   3*L'VPARM
                                    1209              *        ARG5     EQU   4*L'VPARM
                                    1210              *        ARG6     EQU   5*L'VPARM
                                    1211              *
                                    1212              *        FNRET    EQU   0*L'VPARM           USUALLY @R6
                                    1213              *
                                    1214              *
                                    1215              *        FNWA     RECORD BEGIN ,            GENERALIZED WORK AREA !
                                    1216              *        FNWORK   DS    XL(L'VPARM)         256+ BYTE WORK AREA
                                    1217              *                 END
                                    1218              *        ******************** OH YEAH !!

0                                   8147              *
                                    8148              *
                                    8149              *   LOCAL MACROS
                                    8150              *
                                    8151              *        SETARGS - SET ARG TYPES
                                    8152              *        RETARGS - RETURN PROCEDURE ARGS
                                    8153              *        VRETURN - RETURN VARIABLE VALUE, TYPE
                                    8154              *        BADARG - CREATE BAD ARGUMENT MESSAGE
                                    8155              *
                                    8156              *.... ..   -... ..- -..
-                                   8158              *
                                    8159              *                               SET ARGUMENT TYPES
                                    8160                       MACRO
                                    8161              &L       SETARGS  &LIST
                                    8162              &L       LA    R2,=C&LIST          LIST OF ARGUMENT TYPES TO SET
                                    8163                       ACALL SETARGS             R1 - ARG LIST, R0 - ARG COUNT
                                    8164                       MEND
-                                   8166              *
                                    8167              *                             RETURN VARIABLE @R6
                                    8168                       MACRO
                                    8169              &L       VRETURN &TYPE,&VALUE,&LEN
                                    8170              &L       DS    0H
                                    8171                       AIF   ('&TYPE' EQ 'STRING').TYPESTR
                                    8172                       AIF   ('&TYPE' EQ 'INTEGER').TYPEINT
                                    8173                       AIF   ('&TYPE' EQ 'LINENO').TYPELNO
                                    8174                       AIF   ('&TYPE' EQ 'BOOLEAN').TYPEBOOL
                                    8175                       MNOTE 8,'INVALID TYPE SPECIFIED'
                                    8176              .*
                                    8177              .*                                 RETURN STRING VALUE
                                    8178              .TYPESTR ANOP
                                    8179                       WITH  (VNENTRY,R6),BEGIN
                                    8180                       CLEAR VNENTRY                 CLEAR ENTRY
                                    8181                       SET   VNSTRING                SET STRING TYPE
                                    8182                       SETMSG &VALUE,&LEN
                                    8183                       STH   R0,VNSTRLEN             SAVE STRING LEN
                                    8184                       LTR   R3,R0                   SAVE STRING VALUE
                                    8185                       IF    POS,BEGIN
                                    8186                       DEX   R3,' MVC VNSTRLOC(0),@R1 '
                                    8187                       END
                                    8188                       SR    R15,R15
                                    8189                       END   , WITH (VNENTRY,R6)
                                    8190                       MEXIT
                                    8191              .*                                 RETURN INTEGER VALUE
                                    8192              .TYPEINT ANOP
                                    8193                       WITH  (VNENTRY,R6),BEGIN
                                    8194                       CLEAR VNENTRY                 CLEAR ENTRY
                                    8195                       SET   VNNUMB                  SET NUMBER TYPE
                                    8196                       $L    R1,&VALUE,OP=LA         SET VALUE
                                    8197                       ST    R1,VNVALUE
                                    8198                       LA    R2,VNENTRY

                                    8356              *
                                    8357              *  GTFNRTN - GET SYSTEM FUNCTION ROUTINE ADDRESS
                                    8358              *
                                    8359              *  ON ENTRY:
                                    8360              *    @R0 - PLACE TO RETURN ROUTINE ADDRESS
                                    8361              *    @R1 - FUNCTION NAME, LEFT JUSTIFIED BLANK PADDED
                                    8362              *
                                    8363              *  ON EXIT:
                                    8364              *    R15=Z, ROUTINE FOUND;  R15=NZ, ROUTINE NOT FOUND

                                    8367              *

0                                  58291              ¿þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþÜ
                                   58292              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   58293              Ÿ  ARRAY_SEARCH( array, string [,cnt] [,flags] [,min] [,pos] [,size] )I
                                   58294              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   58295              Ÿ   search "array[1] to array[cnt]" for "string", if "cnt" is 0 or    Ÿ
                                   58296              Ÿ     omitted search the whole array.  Returns the index into the     Ÿ
                                   58297              Ÿ     array or 0 if a match is not found. Flags are as follows:       Ÿ
                                   58298              Ÿ        01  Case insensitive compare                                 Ÿ
                                   58299              Ÿ        02  Abbreviation is allowed                                  Ÿ
                                   58300              Ÿ        04  Use a linear search (array is not sorted)                Ÿ
                                   58301              Ÿ        08  Perform a stem-search (array must be sorted)             Ÿ
                                   58302              Ÿ     If abbreviation is allowed then a positive "min" indicates the  Ÿ
                                   58303              Ÿ     minimum abbreviation allowed.  "Pos" and "size" delimit the     Ÿ
                                   58304              Ÿ     portion of each string of array to be compared, they default to Ÿ
                                   58305              Ÿ     1 and "to the end" respectively.                                Ÿ
                                   58306              Ÿ     If a stem-search is being performed "min" is the last element ofI
                                   58307              Ÿ     array searched (i.e., start searching at array[min+1]).         Ÿ
                                   58308              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   58309              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»
